{"id":"quant-ph/0511040","submitter":"Debasis Sarkar","authors":"Indrani Chattopadhyay and Debasis Sarkar","title":"Impossibility of Exact Flipping of Three Arbitrary Quantum States Via\n  Incomparability","comments":"9 pages, no figures, replaced with accepted version, Phys. Rev. A","journal-ref":"Phys. Rev. A 73, 044303 (2006)","doi":"10.1103/PhysRevA.73.044303","report-no":null,"categories":"quant-ph","license":null,"abstract":"  We present here a scheme that relates seemingly two different kinds of\nphysical impossibilities of quantum information processing. We derive, exact\nflipping of three arbitrary states not lying in one great circle is not\npossible with certainty, by using the existence of incomparable states which\nare not interconvertible deterministically by local operations and classical\ncommunications. In contrast, considering the non-existence of exact universal\nflipper, the incomparability of a pair of bipartite pure entangled states can\nbe established.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 4 Nov 2005 11:31:37 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 14 Apr 2006 20:29:51 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-11"}
